Introduction

This assignment is designed to introduce you to the basics of Quarto. You will learn how to create documents with headers, formatted text, lists, tables, and embed R code for data analysis. Import YAML

It is crucial to include embed-resources: true in the YAML header when you generate HTML files (and revealjs slides). For this document, theme: yeti and code-line-numbers: true was used.

Check out date: and date-format: options to properly format the date.

Objectives

  • Understand and apply Quarto markdown formatting
  • Embed and execute R code within a Quarto document

Embedding R Code

Quarto allows embedding R code blocks for dynamic analysis and reporting. For below code, make sure not to print warning messages with #| warning: false.

For slides, including

  • auto-stretch: false and
  • scrollable: true

in the YAML header will ensure that all content is presented without any compression or omission of images.

library(tidyquant)
library(tidyverse)
aapl_data <- tq_get("AAPL", from = "2020-01-01", to = "2020-12-31")

# Plot candlestick chart
aapl_data %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = date, open = open, high = high, low = low, close = close)) +
  geom_candlestick() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "AAPL Candlestick Chart 2020", x = "Date", y = "Price (USD)")
